What nice about HATEOAS is that you can inject commentary, system status,
whatever you like if you&#39;re using HTML.  This additional information helps
those in meatspace[1] understand and interact with your resources.  I&#39;ve
used javascript to provide interactivity when a representation is sent to
the client.  The sweet part is that the agents are processing the link/rel
tags and never care about the javascript or surrounding html.  Microformats
help here as well.  Since these were specific to the application, I didn&#39;t
have to bother with defining new media types.
I&#39;ve been asked/challenged on what is the WSDL equivalent for RESTful
architecture is and my answer included the above plus the need for the agent
to query.  Querying the document for links/rel tags allows for arbitrary
content to be included which I believe is a good thing and promoted the
pattern above.  WADL/WSDL is much too brittle for my taste because these
techniques rely on ordinal positions or link templates to navigate the
hypermedia.  I&#39;ve blogged about the need to query here [2].

-Noah

[1] http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meatspace
[2] http://noahcampbell.info/?p=203

